05/10/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX police on Monday (October 4th) arrested a Serb in northern Mitrovica suspected of committing several crimes, including attempted murder.
Media identified the suspect as Dejan Vulovic.
The mission announced that the suspect faces charges related to attempted murder, unauthorised possession of weapons and causing general danger.
He is also the subject of an international arrest warrant.
This is the first EULEX operation in the north since the mission deployed in December 2008.
(Koha Ditore, Express, Telegrafi, Top Channel - 05/10/10;
Kohavision, RTK - 04/10/10)
